# NestJS Backend Structure

- Keep NestJS modules organized by feature. Place controllers, services, DTOs, and feature tests together in the feature area when it fits the scaffold.
- Controllers should handle HTTP routing and request/response boundaries only. Put validation, authorization decisions, and business behavior in services or focused helpers.
- Use DTOs for request and response shapes that cross module or HTTP boundaries. Keep persistence or transport details out of controllers.
- Avoid large services. Extract focused providers/helpers when a service grows multiple unrelated responsibilities.
- Add unit tests for service behavior and integration-style tests for HTTP endpoints when a scaffold adds or changes backend behavior.
